Use the mcp__blackboard__write_blackboard tool to write the following HTML content to the file "cbt-submission-brief.html". The idea ID context is "coworking-space-in-rossland-bc".

Write this exact HTML content:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Rossland Works — CBT Submission Brief</title>
<style>
  :root {
    --bg:#f5f2ee;--surface:#fff;--surface2:#f0ede8;--border:#d0c8bc;
    --accent:#8a6a1f;--al:#c9a84c;--text:#1a1a1a;--muted:#6b6560;
    --danger:#9a3527;--green:#1a8a60;--blue:#1a5f9a;
  }
  @media(prefers-color-scheme:dark){
    :root{--bg:#0d1117;--surface:#161b22;--surface2:#1c2330;--border:#30363d;
    --accent:#c9a84c;--al:#c9a84c;--text:#e6edf3;--muted:#8b949e;
    --danger:#c85a4a;--green:#3fb68d;--blue:#4a8fc9;}
  }
  *{box-sizing:border-box;margin:0;padding:0;}
  body{font-family:Arial,sans-serif;background:var(--bg);color:var(--text);font-size:14px;line-height:1.7;}
  .cover{background:linear-gradient(160deg,#1a2535,#0d1117 50%,#1a2010);padding:64px;position:relative;overflow:hidden;}
  .cover::before{content:'';position:absolute;inset:0;background:radial-gradient(ellipse at 10% 80%,rgba(201,168,76,.12),transparent 50%),radial-gradient(ellipse at 90% 20%,rgba(63,182,141,.06),transparent 50%);}
  .cover-tag{font-size:10px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:.35em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#c9a84c;margin-bottom:18px;position:relative;}
  .cover h1{font-size:46px;font-weight:300;color:#e6edf3;letter-spacing:-.03em;line-height:1.1;margin-bottom:10px;position:relative;}
  .cover h1 span{color:#c9a84c;}
  .cover-sub{font-size:14px;color:#8b949e;max-width:480px;position:relative;margin-bottom:32px;}
  .cover-meta{display:flex;gap:36px;flex-wrap:wrap;position:relative;}
  .ml{font-size:9px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:.25em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#8b949e;margin-bottom:3px;}
  .mv{font-size:13px;font-weight:600;color:#c9a84c;}
  .gold-bar{height:3px;background:linear-gradient(90deg,#c9a84c,transparent);}
  .main{max-width:880px;margin:0 auto;padding:52px 64px 80px;}
  .sl{font-size:9px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:.35em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted);margin:48px 0 18px;padding-bottom:10px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);}
  .intro{font-size:15px;line-height:1.8;color:var(--text);margin-bottom:24px;}
  .lead{font-size:14px;color:var(--text);margin-bottom:14px;}
  .sub{font-size:12px;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:12px;line-height:1.6;}
  .doc-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr 1fr;gap:14px;margin:18px 0;}
  .doc-card{background:var(--surface);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:8px;padding:20px 16px;}
  .doc-let{width:36px;height:36px;border-radius:6px;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-size:15px;font-weight:800;margin-bottom:11px;}
  .doc-title{font-size:13px;font-weight:700;color:var(--text);margin-bottom:5px;}
  .doc-desc{font-size:12px;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.5;margin:0;}
  .doc-file{font-size:10px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted);margin-top:9px;}
  .sg{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr 1fr;gap:14px;margin:18px 0;}
  .sc{background:var(--surface);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:8px;padding:20px 16px;}
  .sn{font-size:10px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:12px;}
  .sr{font-size:26px;font-weight:300;color:var(--al);line-height:1;margin-bottom:3px;}
  .srl{font-size:10px;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:12px;}
  .st{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;font-size:12px;padding:4px 0;border-top:1px solid var(--border);}
  .stl{color:var(--muted);}
  .stv{font-weight:700;}
  .pos{color:var(--green)!important;}
  .neg{color:var(--danger)!important;}
  table{width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;font-size:13px;margin:16px 0;}
  th{background:var(--surface2);color:var(--muted);font-size:10px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;padding:9px 13px;text-align:left;border-bottom:2px solid var(--border);}
  td{padding:10px 13px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);color:var(--text);vertical-align:top;}
  .tr td{font-weight:700;background:var(--surface2);border-top:2px solid var(--border);}
  .cl{list-style:none;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:8px;margin:18px 0;}
  .cli{display:flex;gap:11px;align-items:flex-start;background:var(--surface);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:7px;padding:12px 14px;}
  .cc{width:19px;height:19px;border-radius:50%;border:2px solid var(--border);flex-shrink:0;margin-top:1px;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;}
  .cc.done{background:var(--green);border-color:var(--green);}
  .ct{flex:1;}
  .ctitle{font-weight:700;color:var(--text);display:block;margin-bottom:2px;font-size:13px;}
  .cdet{color:var(--muted);font-size:12px;line-height:1.5;}
  .cb{flex-shrink:0;font-size:9px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:.12em;text-transform:uppercase;padding:3px 7px;border-radius:3px;align-self:flex-start;margin-top:2px;}
  .bdone{background:rgba(26,138,96,.12);color:var(--green);}
  .bnext{background:rgba(138,106,31,.12);color:var(--accent);}
  .blater{background:rgba(26,95,154,.12);color:var(--blue);}
  .rr{display:flex;gap:11px;align-items:flex-start;padding:12px 0;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);}
  .rr:last-child{border-bottom:none;}
  .rp{flex-shrink:0;padding:3px 9px;border-radius:10px;font-size:9px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;white-space:nowrap;margin-top:2px;}
  .rh{background:rgba(154,53,39,.12);color:var(--danger);}
  .rm{background:rgba(138,106,31,.12);color:var(--accent);}
  .rl{background:rgba(26,138,96,.12);color:var(--green);}
  .rtitle{font-weight:700;color:var(--text);display:block;margin-bottom:2px;font-size:13px;}
  .rmit{color:var(--muted);font-size:12px;line-height:1.5;}
  .tl{padding-left:30px;position:relative;}
  .tl::before{content:'';position:absolute;left:7px;top:18px;bottom:18px;width:2px;background:var(--border);}
  .tli{position:relative;margin-bottom:22px;}
  .tld{position:absolute;left:-30px;top:1px;width:17px;height:17px;border-radius:50%;border:2px solid var(--al);background:var(--surface);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-size:9px;font-weight:800;color:var(--al);}
  .tlw{font-size:10px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:.15em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:3px;}
  .tla{font-size:13px;font-weight:700;color:var(--text);margin-bottom:3px;}
  .tldet{font-size:12px;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.5;}
  .nb{margin-top:40px;padding:22px 26px;background:var(--surface);border:1px solid var(--border);border-left:4px solid var(--al);border-radius:8px;}
  .nb-title{font-size:13px;font-weight:700;color:var(--text);margin-bottom:7px;}
  .nb p{font-size:13px;color:var(--muted);margin:0;line-height:1.7;}
  .footer{background:var(--surface2);border-top:1px solid var(--border);padding:26px 64px;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:12px;font-size:11px;color:var(--muted);}
  .flogo{font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:var(--al);letter-spacing:-.02em;margin-bottom:3px;}
  @media(max-width:640px){.cover,.main,.footer{padding-left:24px;padding-right:24px;}.doc-grid,.sg{grid-template-columns:1fr;}.footer{flex-direction:column;}}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="cover">
  <div class="cover-tag">CBT Submission Package</div>
  <h1>Rossland <span>Works</span></h1>
  <p class="cover-sub">A coworking space for Rossland's remote workers, entrepreneurs, and small businesses — developed in partnership with Columbia Basin Trust.</p>
  <div class="cover-meta">
    <div><div class="ml">Location</div><div class="mv">Rossland, BC</div></div>
    <div><div class="ml">Space</div><div class="mv">1,800 sq ft</div></div>
    <div><div class="ml">Capital Required</div><div class="mv">$61,500 – $117,000</div></div>
    <div><div class="ml">CBT Funding Sought</div><div class="mv">$50,000 – $115,000</div></div>
    <div><div class="ml">Prepared</div><div class="mv">March 2026</div></div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="gold-bar"></div>

<div class="main">

<p class="intro">This document is the submission guide for the Rossland Works CBT funding application. It maps the supporting documents, summarizes the financial case, and gives the founder a clear sequence of steps before the formal application is filed.</p>

<div class="sl">Submission Package — Three Annexes</div>
<p class="lead">Submit all three documents together to CBT's Impact Investment Fund. Each stands alone but is designed to be read as a set.</p>
<div class="doc-grid">
  <div class="doc-card">
    <div class="doc-let" style="background:rgba(138,106,31,.1);color:#8a6a1f">A</div>
    <div class="doc-title">Business Plan</div>
    <p class="doc-desc">Market analysis, community need, membership structure, operations model, and CBT partnership rationale. Covers Rossland and Trail context, target member profiles, and C3 governance option.</p>
    <div class="doc-file">business-plan.html</div>
  </div>
  <div class="doc-card">
    <div class="doc-let" style="background:rgba(26,138,96,.1);color:#1a8a60">B</div>
    <div class="doc-title">Financial Model</div>
    <p class="doc-desc">Three-year projections across three scenarios. Startup capital and funding source tables. All KPI figures verified against detailed tables. Revenue stated net of GST. Add-ons revenue itemized by component.</p>
    <div class="doc-file">financial-model.html</div>
  </div>
  <div class="doc-card">
    <div class="doc-let" style="background:rgba(26,95,154,.1);color:#1a5f9a">C</div>
    <div class="doc-title">Launch Roadmap</div>
    <p class="doc-desc">Four-phase execution plan with go/no-go gates at Month 3 and Month 6. CBT milestone reporting schedule, risk register with mitigations, 14-item pre-opening checklist.</p>
    <div class="doc-file">launch-roadmap.html</div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="sl">Financial Scenarios at a Glance</div>
<p class="lead">All scenarios assume 1,800 sq ft at $1,800/mo, a part-time community manager starting at 80 hrs/mo, and a 7-month pre-opening period. Year 1 figures cover the first full operating year. All revenue is net of GST.</p>
<div class="sg">
  <div class="sc">
    <div class="sn">Conservative</div>
    <div class="sr">$46,412</div>
    <div class="srl">Year 1 Revenue</div>
    <div class="st"><span class="stl">Y1 Net</span><span class="stv neg">($12,508)</span></div>
    <div class="st"><span class="stl">Y2 Net</span><span class="stv pos">+$5,960</span></div>
    <div class="st"><span class="stl">Y3 Net</span><span class="stv pos">+$22,864</span></div>
    <div class="st"><span class="stl">Avg Members Y1</span><span class="stv">15</span></div>
    <div class="st"><span class="stl">Break-Even</span><span class="stv">Month 22</span></div>
  </div>
  <div class="sc" style="border-color:var(--al)">
    <div class="sn" style="color:var(--accent)">Realistic — Base Case</div>
    <div class="sr">$87,632</div>
    <div class="srl">Year 1 Revenue</div>
    <div class="st"><span class="stl">Y1 Net</span><span class="stv pos">+$28,712</span></div>
    <div class="st"><span class="stl">Y2 Net</span><span class="stv pos">+$63,228</span></div>
    <div class="st"><span class="stl">Y3 Net</span><span class="stv pos">+$86,336</span></div>
    <div class="st"><span class="stl">Avg Members Y1</span><span class="stv">25</span></div>
    <div class="st"><span class="stl">Break-Even</span><span class="stv">Month 6-8*</span></div>
  </div>
  <div class="sc">
    <div class="sn">Optimistic</div>
    <div class="sr">$137,056</div>
    <div class="srl">Year 1 Revenue</div>
    <div class="st"><span class="stl">Y1 Net</span><span class="stv pos">+$74,836</span></div>
    <div class="st"><span class="stl">Y2 Net</span><span class="stv pos">+$114,232</span></div>
    <div class="st"><span class="stl">Y3 Net</span><span class="stv pos">+$144,980</span></div>
    <div class="st"><span class="stl">Avg Members Y1</span><span class="stv">40</span></div>
    <div class="st"><span class="stl">Break-Even</span><span class="stv">Month 3-4</span></div>
  </div>
</div>
<p class="sub">*Realistic break-even conditional on 15 founding members signed before opening. CBT loan repayment not included in net figures — see Annex B for detail.</p>

<div class="sl">Funding Strategy</div>
<table>
  <thead><tr><th>Source</th><th>Type</th><th>Target</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td><strong>CBT Impact Investment Fund</strong> — primary application; low/no interest; community benefit criteria met by economic development and remote work retention rationale</td><td>Repayable loan</td><td>$50,000–$75,000</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>CBT Working Capital Loan</strong> — supplements Impact Investment Fund or serves as bridge; faster approval cycle</td><td>Repayable loan</td><td>Up to $40,000</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>Founding Member Pre-Sales</strong> — 15 charter members at $75/mo x 12 months; non-dilutive; also validates demand for CBT application</td><td>Revenue</td><td>$13,500</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>REDI Grant (RDKB)</strong> — Regional Economic Development Initiative; investigate eligibility with RDKB Economic Development</td><td>Grant (if eligible)</td><td>$5,000–$20,000</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>Founder Investment</strong> — demonstrates commitment; reduces loan-to-equity ratio</td><td>Equity</td><td>$10,000–$20,000</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>Columbia Basin Credit Union</strong> — parallel path if CBT is delayed; open relationship before you need a decision</td><td>Conventional loan</td><td>Supplement as needed</td></tr>
    <tr class="tr"><td>Combined funding capacity</td><td></td><td>$78,500–$168,500</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<div class="sl">Pre-Submission Checklist</div>
<p class="lead">Items marked Done are complete in the prepared package. The rest require action by the founder before submitting.</p>
<ul class="cl">
  <li class="cli">
    <div class="cc done"><svg width="10" height="10" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="white" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20,6 9,17 4,12"/></svg></div>
    <div class="ct"><span class="ctitle">Business plan written (Annex A)</span><span class="cdet">Market analysis, membership structure, operations, CBT rationale, and risk register complete.</span></div>
    <span class="cb bdone">Done</span>
  </li>
  <li class="cli">
    <div class="cc done"><svg width="10" height="10" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="white" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20,6 9,17 4,12"/></svg></div>
    <div class="ct"><span class="ctitle">Financial model prepared and verified (Annex B)</span><span class="cdet">Three scenarios with verified KPIs, startup capital table, funding sources, GST treatment noted, add-ons revenue itemized by component.</span></div>
    <span class="cb bdone">Done</span>
  </li>
  <li class="cli">
    <div class="cc done"><svg width="10" height="10" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="white" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20,6 9,17 4,12"/></svg></div>
    <div class="ct"><span class="ctitle">Launch roadmap prepared (Annex C)</span><span class="cdet">Four-phase plan with milestone gates, CBT reporting schedule, risk register, and pre-opening checklist complete.</span></div>
    <span class="cb bdone">Done</span>
  </li>
  <li class="cli">
    <div class="cc"></div>
    <div class="ct"><span class="ctitle">Register the legal entity</span><span class="cdet">Incorporate a BC corporation or Community Contribution Company (C3) and obtain a CRA business number. Budget $1,500-3,000. CBT cannot process a loan application without a registered entity.</span></div>
    <span class="cb bnext">Do First</span>
  </li>
  <li class="cli">
    <div class="cc"></div>
    <div class="ct"><span class="ctitle">Book introductory meeting with CBT Basin Advisor</span><span class="cdet">Present Annexes A and B. Get informal feedback before the formal application enters the queue. A letter of interest from CBT accelerates review significantly. cbt.org/businesses</span></div>
    <span class="cb bnext">Do First</span>
  </li>
  <li class="cli">
    <div class="cc"></div>
    <div class="ct"><span class="ctitle">Run community demand survey</span><span class="cdet">2 weeks, targeting Rossland and Trail remote workers. Target 50+ responses and 15+ soft commitments. Attach results as an appendix to the CBT application — they are evidence of community support.</span></div>
    <span class="cb bnext">Do First</span>
  </li>
  <li class="cli">
    <div class="cc"></div>
    <div class="ct"><span class="ctitle">Collect letters of support</span><span class="cdet">City of Rossland Economic Development, Rossland Chamber, RDKB. Even brief acknowledgement letters carry weight in CBT's community benefit evaluation criteria.</span></div>
    <span class="cb bnext">Do First</span>
  </li>
  <li class="cli">
    <div class="cc"></div>
    <div class="ct"><span class="ctitle">Shortlist 3 candidate spaces</span><span class="cdet">Document floor plans, lease rates, and landlord flexibility. Confirm layouts accommodate 12+ open desks, meeting room, and 1-2 private offices. Attach shortlist to the application.</span></div>
    <span class="cb bnext">Do First</span>
  </li>
  <li class="cli">
    <div class="cc"></div>
    <div class="ct"><span class="ctitle">Submit CBT application</span><span class="cdet">Full package: Annexes A, B, C plus survey results, support letters, space shortlist, and entity documents. Apply for Working Capital Loan simultaneously. Allow 60-90 days for review.</span></div>
    <span class="cb blater">After Prep</span>
  </li>
  <li class="cli">
    <div class="cc"></div>
    <div class="ct"><span class="ctitle">Inquire about REDI Grant and open Columbia Basin Credit Union relationship</span><span class="cdet">Non-repayable REDI grant if eligible. CBCU as a parallel financing path. Open both relationships before you need a decision from either.</span></div>
    <span class="cb blater">Parallel Track</span>
  </li>
</ul>

<div class="sl">Top Risks for CBT Review</div>
<div>
  <div class="rr">
    <div class="rp rh">High</div>
    <div><span class="rtitle">Small population — Rossland has ~4,100 residents</span><span class="rmit">Addressed in business plan: meeting room and event revenue draws from Trail (~8,000 residents, 15 min away) and Warfield. Non-member revenue is modelled conservatively. The realistic scenario is defensible with Trail market access.</span></div>
  </div>
  <div class="rr">
    <div class="rp rh">High</div>
    <div><span class="rtitle">Demand risk — unproven coworking market in Rossland</span><span class="rmit">Mitigated by demand survey and founding member pre-sales (15 sign-ups before opening). Present survey results and pre-sales data with the application. Pre-sales provide $13,500 in pre-revenue and are direct proof of demand.</span></div>
  </div>
  <div class="rr">
    <div class="rp rm">Medium</div>
    <div><span class="rtitle">Seasonality — some Rossland activity is ski-dependent</span><span class="rmit">Member base targets year-round remote workers, not seasonal ski workers. Trail corporate accounts, virtual memberships, and summer programming provide off-season baseline. Conservative scenario accounts for seasonal softness.</span></div>
  </div>
  <div class="rr">
    <div class="rp rl">Low</div>
    <div><span class="rtitle">Competition — no coworking space currently exists in Rossland</span><span class="rmit">No direct competitor as of March 2026. Nearest comparable is in Castlegar. First-mover position with Red Mountain Resort proximity is a durable local advantage.</span></div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="sl">Recommended Sequence</div>
<div class="tl">
  <div class="tli">
    <div class="tld">1</div>
    <div class="tlw">Week 1-2</div>
    <div class="tla">Launch demand survey and register legal entity</div>
    <div class="tldet">Start the survey immediately — 2 weeks of data. Incorporate the entity in parallel. C3 structure may strengthen CBT application. Budget $1,500-3,000 for BC counsel familiar with C3 structures.</div>
  </div>
  <div class="tli">
    <div class="tld">2</div>
    <div class="tlw">Week 3-4</div>
    <div class="tla">CBT Basin Advisor meeting — present Annexes A and B</div>
    <div class="tldet">Bring preliminary survey results. Ask for informal feedback before formal submission. Advisors know what CBT reviewers prioritize — use this meeting to learn that before filing.</div>
  </div>
  <div class="tli">
    <div class="tld">3</div>
    <div class="tlw">Week 4-6</div>
    <div class="tla">Collect support letters and shortlist candidate spaces</div>
    <div class="tldet">Contact City of Rossland, Rossland Chamber, and RDKB. Visit properties and document lease rates. Both inputs are standard CBT requirements and take time to gather.</div>
  </div>
  <div class="tli">
    <div class="tld">4</div>
    <div class="tlw">Week 6-8</div>
    <div class="tla">Submit CBT Impact Investment Fund application</div>
    <div class="tldet">Attach all three annexes, survey results, support letters, space shortlist, and entity documents. File Working Capital Loan application simultaneously. CBT review: 60-90 days.</div>
  </div>
  <div class="tli">
    <div class="tld">5</div>
    <div class="tlw">Month 3 — CBT Decision</div>
    <div class="tla">Go/No-Go: sign lease conditional on funding confirmation</div>
    <div class="tldet">If approved: sign lease and begin fit-out per Annex C. If delayed: activate Columbia Basin Credit Union bridge loan. The launch roadmap takes over from this point with a week-by-week pre-launch plan.</div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="nb">
  <div class="nb-title">On the CBT Community Benefit Test</div>
  <p>CBT's Impact Investment Fund is a repayable loan — it requires demonstrable community or economic benefit to Basin residents. The strongest angle for Rossland Works: enabling remote workers to stay in or relocate to Rossland rather than commuting to Trail or leaving the region for larger cities. Frame every CBT conversation around that story. A coworking space that keeps five professional families in Rossland is a compelling Basin-benefit case. Pair this with the demand survey data and founding member pre-sales, and the application has a strong factual foundation.</p>
</div>

</div>

<div class="footer">
  <div>
    <div class="flogo">Rossland Works</div>
    <div>CBT Submission Package — March 2026 | Annexes A, B, C included</div>
  </div>
  <div style="text-align:right">All revenue figures net of GST.<br>CBT loan repayment not modelled in projections.</div>
</div>

</body>
</html>
```

Please write exactly this content to the blackboard file "cbt-submission-brief.html". Return the result of the write operation.
